The paper proposes a deep reinforcement learning framework for estimating optimal dynamic treatment regimes from observational medical data. This involves modeling real-life complexity in disease progression and treatment choices, with the goal of providing personalized decision recommendations. The paper uses deep neural networks for both supervised learning and reinforcement learning steps. Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-categories are cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science). Additionally, the paper involves working with medical registry data, which could fall under cs.CY (Computers and Society) or cs.DB (Databases).
